post_text:
Our friends at Caroline County Recreation and Parks are helping students get ready for distance learning! #ourvillage
#GrowCaroline
#carolinebts2020
shared_text:
Caroline County Recreation and Parks
September 3 at 5:00 PM ·

It seems like just yesterday we were knee deep in virtual summer camp, so it's hard to believe that the new year for Caroline County Public Schools starts in just 5 days.

We had such a good time making videos this summer that a couple of our camp directors have put together some more videos to help students that are preparing for the start of distance learning. We'll have a new video each weekday for at least the next week.

Today, join Ms. Katie and Ms. Nicole as they share some tips on creating and personalizing your child's workspace.

If you've been enjoying our videos keep an eye out for more content we'll be rolling out soon called REC @ Home, which will bring some of that virtual camp fun into your homes year-round.

post_text: The test event is over but the video will live on! Check out the awesome #LMSWildcat Sneak Preview. 🍿🥤 🤩 👏👏👏
shared_text:
Lockerman Middle School
September 3 at 11:34 AM ·

Lockerman Middle School families,

Don't forget that our "Test the System" event is taking place at 1:00 PM today. A link to a Zoom meeting should have been sent out by your child's first period teacher. Please have your child check their CCPS Gmail account and/or the Google Classroom of their first period teacher to locate the link.

Day one of laptop distribution is taking place until 6:00 PM today. We will also have laptop and spply distribution on Friday from 8:00 AM- 6:00 PM. It has been great to meet some of our incoming wildcats and see the faces of those we have missed seeing.

As a reminder, the Flipgrid "Meet the Teacher" night will take place on Friday at 6:30 PM. Links to the Flipgrid teacher introductions will be sent out via School Messenger email, accessible on our LMS facebook page, and posted on our website (lockermams.org). Here is a sneak peek of some of the creative ways our teachers are introducing themselves to your students. Huge shout out to the 8th grade ELA team.

post_text: This photo and message speaks volumes about so much of our #CarolineSummer.
shared_text:
Lockerman Middle School
September 2 at 3:53 PM ·

This image truly does not capture the hard work and time commitment put forth by our technology department, custodial staff, nursing staff, secretaries, teachers, counselors, and administration. 900+ individually organized supply kits and student folders, 700+ laptops with more to come for those that are still waiting, locker items left behind, awards from last year, and even a few yearbooks that were not picked up. Be patient with us tomorrow and Friday as we work to distribute these items to you. The LMS staff will be all hands on deck to move you through as quickly as we can. Wildcats, we are ready for you! #TheShowMustGoOn #WildcatPRIDE

shared_text:
Greensboro Elementary School
September 3 at 12:07 PM ·

🐝Attention 4th & 5th Grade Families🐝
We are monitoring the weather closely and due to predicted storms this evening, tonight’s Meet the Teacher for 4th & 5th grade families will begin at 3:00pm. Again, this is a drive through event held at Greater Impact Church across the street from the school.
If weather becomes severe we will stop the event and reschedule distribution of materials on Friday, September 4th between 9:00am-4:00pm at GES.

Estamos monitoreando el clima de cerca y debido a las tormentas pronosticadas esta noche, la reunión Conozca al maestro para las familias de 4to y 5to grado comenzará a las 3:00 pm. Nuevamente, este es un evento de unidad que se lleva a cabo en la Iglesia Greater Impact al otro lado de la calle de la escuela.
Si el clima se vuelve severo, detendremos el evento y reprogramaremos la distribución de materiales para el viernes 4 de septiembre entre las 9:00 am y las 4:00 pm.

shared_text:
Preston Elementary School
September 3 at 12:39 PM ·

Dear Preston Elementary School families,￼

Due to a fiber outage in the Preston area that directly connects Preston Elementary School to its Internet capabilities we will have to cancel the technology test for today for all Preston Elementary School families￼. I apologize for the inconvenience and for the late notice, we were very hopeful that it would be solved in time for the tech test. Please be assured that this issue will be solved by the end of our day today, and we will still have our Meet the Teacher virtual zoom hours from 1 to 3 PM on Friday, September 4.￼

shared_text:
Caroline County Public Library
August 28 at 9:05 AM ·

We now offer online Tech Help from 11 am - 6 pm on weekdays and 10 am - 2 pm on Saturdays. Anyone with a technology-related question can visit www.carolib.org and click the green button to chat with staff. The library can help you:

-Learn about your phone, tablet, or computer, including the laptops available for checkout
-Find no-cost online tutoring for your child
-Navigate online job, housing, or support services
-Request items through our Library to Go system

and much more!

Tech help questions are also welcomed at 410-479-1343 x106. A librarian will take your information, and tech help staff will call you back.

Please note the procedure for Public Comment:
Regarding Public Comment: Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, attendance at meetings is restricted. To ensure the opportunity for public input, the Board will accept written public comment via email sent to pio@ccpsstaff.org. Emails must be received no later than noon on the day of the Board meeting, and must clearly state in the subject line or body of the email “For Public Comment.” Emails will be provided to Board members prior to the start of the meeting, and the content will be included in the Board minutes that follow the meeting.

Greensboro Elementary School
August 25 at 2:14 PM ·

🐝 Attention GES Families 🐝
We are excited to announce our Drive Through Meet the Teacher events scheduled for next week at Greater Impact Church!
▪️ On the designated date, your child will meet his or her teacher for the 2020-2021 school year!
▪️ During this event K-4th grade students will receive a county assigned iPad and 5th grade students will receive a county assigned laptop.
▪️ A virtual meet the teacher event is scheduled for Friday, September 4th from 2:00-3:00 via Zoom. We encourage all students to attend using their new device!

We cannot wait to see our GES Hornets and gear up for an exciting school year!

post_text: Check it out! Thank you to Tidewater Times and Mike Valliant for a superb article on "all things Culinary Arts in Caroline County". That's how we #GrowCaroline!
shared_text:
Mike Valliant
July 27 at 6:37 AM ·

Over the past few years, I have been blown away by the Chesapeake Culinary Center and how in the Caroline Schoolhouse, they can bring together everything from career training through Caroline County Public Schools; house and run Shore Gourmet Denton Market; work with farmers and innovators; process local food to go into the schools; and feed students and senior citizens during a pandemic. They are a blueprint for something every county in the state would do well to replicate. So I was excited when Tidewater Times asked me to write about them, and I might have already known some folks there and a bit of the back story :) I caught up with Beth Brewster and David Murray to talk about all things culinary arts in Caroline County. You can find copies of the August issue around the Shore, and/or read the article here: https://issuu.com/tidewatertimes/docs/august_2020_tidewater_times_web_magazine/43

Governor Larry Hogan
July 19 at 10:02 AM ·

After a record 28,899 COVID-19 tests reported in the past 24 hours, Maryland’s daily positivity is 3.83% with a seven-day average of 4.46%. There are 449 current total hospitalizations.

Nearly half of new cases belong to Marylanders in their 20s and 30s, and the positivity rate for Marylanders under 35 is over 85% higher than Marylanders 35 and older. We are urging younger Marylanders to take these statistics seriously: this pandemic is by no means behind us.

Our recovery depends on each and every Marylander exercising personal responsibility. Wear a mask in indoor public areas, practice physical distancing, and avoid large gatherings.

We encourage anyone interested to get tested for COVID-19, particularly those who have recently traveled or engaged in high-risk activities. Plan your test today by visiting covidtest.maryland.gov.

Being a Virtual Summer Camper doesn't mean your child will be in front of a screen all day. In fact, we designed the program to do the opposite. shared_text:
Caroline County Public Library
June 30 at 2:11 PM ·

A group of 23 artists, who live or work in Easton, will have an art show along the fence at 11 South Aurora Street on July 4. Each artist will portray a chosen African American who has unjustly lost his or her life because of systemic racism in the U.S. The show will hang on the fence from 10 a.m.-4 p.m. and all are invited to respectfully view from the sidewalk during those hours. The works are not for sale, but the artists hope that the impact from the display will serve to send a collective message that we, as a nation, still have much to do to improve our democracy for all of its citizens.

A group of 23 artists, who live or work in Easton, will have an art show along the fence at 11 South Aurora Street on July 4. The works are not for sale, but the artists hope that the impact from the display will serve to send a collective message that we, as a nation, still have much to do to improve our democracy for all of its citizens.

Caroline's Helping Hands
June 5 at 1:37 AM ·

There will be a Fresh Produce food giveaway this Saturday, June 6, 2020 from 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. at Federalsburg Elementary School.

Also, Denton Christian Church and Living Waters Assembly will combine their Mega Food Giveaways which will take place at Aaron's Place in Denton, MD on June 18th

There will also be another Mega Food Giveaway by Ross Chapel at Aaron's place in Denton on June 24th at 2:00 p.m.

Finally, the following pantries are available on each indicated day of the week which allows for those in need to obtain food every day of the work week.

Aaron's Place II, 435 Main Street Goldsboro, MD 21636 on Sundays from 4 pm - 5 pm & on Mondays from 9 am to 1 pm

Aaron's Place (former Wesleyan School off of Camp Road )
401 Aldersgate Drive, Denton, MD 21629
Tuesdays & Wednesdays from 9 am to 2 pm & on
Thursdays from 9 am to 1 pm

Living Waters Assembly
9058 Double Hills Road, Denton, MD 21629
Wednesdays from 7 pm to 8 pm

Emergency Food Needs are to Call (443) 243-5906 for information on all three locations.

shared_text:
Governor Larry Hogan
May 23 at 4:40 PM ·

On behalf of the people of a proud state, I want to extend our most sincere congratulations to the Class of 2020. The COVID-19 pandemic has required all of us to make incredible sacrifices, including our graduating seniors, but in no way do these unforeseen circumstances lessen your accomplishments or diminish your achievements.

Together, we are going to defeat this deadly virus, and because of the talent and dedication of the members of the Class of 2020, I am incredibly optimistic that the State of Maryland will soon return stronger and better than ever.

Congratulations, stay safe, and may God bless you all.

May is Mental Health Awareness Month.

Mental health is essential to everyone's overall health and well-being. Mental illnesses are common and treatable.

Caroline County will be sharing tools that everyone can use to improve their mental health and increase resiliency regardless of the situations they are dealing with.

COVID-19 has left many of us questioning what is next, but we would like to encourage everyone to remember what you can control during these uncertain times for our community.

#MentalHealthAwarenessMonth
#CarolineStrong

Deadline is midnight May 10 (Sunday)! 94.3 WINX-FM and 96.7 WCEI are honoring seniors by putting your shout-outs on the air starting May 15. Also, Mark Potter will host a Graduation Ceremony on 94.3 WINX-FM beginning at 8 am on May 28.

Create a short audio or video (use your phone or IPad) and email it to mpotter@forevermediainc.com.

So what do you say in a shout-out?
I would like to congratulate Jane Doe on her graduation from ABC High School. We wish you luck at XYZ University in the fall and look forward to seeing what your future holds.

Maybe your child in going to work a trade or going in the military. Simply replace the university.

shared_text:
Pickering Creek Audubon Center
May 6 at 10:24 AM ·

It's blooming in the gardens at Pickering Creek! A pearl crescent butterfly is enjoying a sip from this green and gold (Chrysogonum virginianum). Environmental Earth Science students from Caroline County's Colonel Richardson High School and North Caroline High School planted these little beauties last spring and fall as part of our "Exploring and Restoring Habitats." Thanks to Chesapeake Bay Trust for supporting the project!

Caroline County Economic Development
April 28 at 11:30 AM ·

Did you know, #CarolineCounty, that as a voter, you can check your voter registration, including your residential address, mailing address (if different,) and party affiliation online at: https://tinyurl.com/m5mmpdl

You can also update your information online if you have a valid driver's license: https://tinyurl.com/lsdma9b (This link can be a little confusing because it also allows a user to request an absentee ballot, but you do NOT have to request one in order to update your registration.)

Questions or concerns? please call the Caroline County Board of Elections at 410-479-8145. If you leave a message, they'll return the call as soon as possible.

#carolinecounty #carolinecountymd #carolinecountymaryland #maryland #localbusiness #business #smallbusiness #economicdevelopment #voting #voter

Thank you!

post_text: Some much needed words of wisdom from #CRMSCougars Mr. Honer. #GrowCaroline #CarolineStrong
shared_text:
Rob Honer
April 9 at 11:13 PM ·

I stopped by the school today to pick something up. As I walked up the hallway I noticed the tulips that bloom in the courtyard every year at this time. I chose to look at it in a positive way. I've seen flowers bloom in the courtyard for the last 21 years and they'll continue to bloom. The flowers will be there and the school will be there and when it's our time to go back, we'll be there with our children. However, even though we're not in the building, the flowers do what they have always done. Even though we're not in the building we'll do what we've always done and the children will bloom just like they always have.

shared_text:
Governor Larry Hogan
April 15 at 4:04 PM ·

Today I enacted an executive order which will require the wearing of masks or face coverings when inside any retail establishments, including grocery stores, pharmacies, and convenience stores, or when riding any form of public transportation in Maryland.

It also requires all essential retail locations to require their staff to wear face coverings, and requires those businesses to put appropriate social distancing measures in place in order to keep customers and their staff safe.

To give these retailers time to make these adjustments, the order will go into effect beginning Saturday, April 18, at 7 a.m.

While this order is an important step in our immediate efforts to protect public health and safety, the wearing of masks is also something that we may all have to become more accustomed to in order to safely reopen our state.

The CDC has issued detailed guidance regarding how you can make and use homemade cloth face coverings: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/diy-cloth-face-coverings.html

post_text: Many thanks and much admiration to our 9-1-1 dispatchers! #GrowCaroline #CarolineStrong
shared_text:
Caroline County Government
April 15 at 9:00 AM ·

This week—April 12 - 18, 2018—is National Public Safety Telecommunications Week. It is designated as a time when citizens can recognize the public safety men and women who answer 9-1-1 calls and dispatch the multitude of personnel and equipment during times of crisis.

Caroline County recognizes and acknowledges the 9-1-1 dispatchers and support staff who work tirelessly behind the scenes to help you during emergencies.

Public safety dispatchers may not be out in public, but they are the first line of defense for first responders each and every day, including in the battle against COVID-19. They have been tasked with a tremendous responsibility and they remain ready to answer the call help our Caroline County families through this uncertain time.

We can't say enough about our Dispatchers and the job that they do. Please join us in recognizing their dedication and efforts. If you see a 9-1-1, Police, Fire or EMS /Dispatcher this week thank them for their service to the citizens of Caroline County. They make us #CarolineProud.

Caroline County Economic Development
April 2 at 12:30 PM ·

Scam ALERT: All links from the SBA come with a .GOV

If you receive an email or a link that says SBA [DOT] com or anything but .gov, it is NOT from the SBA.

Also, there are NO fees for any of these loans. The Maryland Dept of Commerce, the SBA or programs in the CARES Act.

If you receive a phone call in reference to the SBA EIDL loan, asking for credit card information, do not provide it. The SBA does NOT do this.

Report such activity to your local SBA office immediately.

#carolinecounty #carolinecountymd #carolinecountymaryland #maryland #localbusiness #business #smallbusiness #economicdevelopment

post_text: Our principals are the best! #GrowCaroline
shared_text:
Antonio Joseph Angeloni
March 27 at 8:11 PM ·

I wanted to just thank all my fellow principals and CCPS BOE staff - the last two weeks have been tough and our dive into virtual learning is going to be a new experience for all of us....but I feel like as a team we have bonded, persevered, and come up with a great plan in uncertain times for all of our kiddos! No one in education got into this to be a rock star or millionaire - we do what we do for kids and the last two weeks reaffirms everything I already knew: I have the best job in the world and I would not want to go through this without the people I am privileged to work with. 😀🙏😊

shared_text:
Children's Mental Health Matters
March 27 at 10:58 AM ·

Starting next Monday, March 30th, in an effort to support children during this unprecedented time of crisis, we will begin offering weekly resources and activities to help support children’s mental health for you to share with the families in your community.

As we all know, managing work while helping children learn and play can be an enormous challenge. We want to also share information for adults as they navigate working from home.

Please check back on Monday to learn more!

Be sure to visit our website, Facebook, Instagram or Twitter accounts or you can subscribe to receive emails directly to your inbox.

📨 Subscribe for Campaign emails: www.bit.ly/2UkL6I1

Until then – remain happy, healthy and hopeful!

#CMHMMaryland #MentalHealthMonday

On Monday, March 30th, we begin Phase I of our Continuity of Learning Plan. Throughout the week, staff will be providing students devices as needed or paper packets, and teaching staff will receive professional development necessary to help students learn remotely. Please click on the post below to see the distribution schedule.

We are so appreciative of the patience and support of our families and community as we continue this difficult journey! We don't have all the answers yet but we are working hard to provide the best possible solutions available for our students. #GrowCaroline

For an A-to-Z COVID-19 resource guide, visit governor.maryland.gov/marylandunites.

post_text: Awe-inspiring work by the Caroline Food Services Team! #GrowCaroline
shared_text:
Beth Wolf Brewster is with David Murray and Samantha Blackmon Figueroa.
March 26 at 8:49 PM ·

This right here is what a community looks like! As I said before my body is sore but my heart is full! I am amazed how this incredible food service staff is cranking out 2400 meals a day ( including a dinner to heat). Organizations pulling together and lending their skills. And the volunteers! Just wow! Delivering food to sites, handing out meals, loading and unloading, filling weekend back packs etc. #teamdavid&sam #carolinerocks #ourkidseatgood
